159;127m[22Cg[38;2;153;153;153m[17C7[m[40;1H [38;2;153;153;153m[1CSearched for [1m3[22m patterns, read [1m3[22m files (ctrl+o to expand)     [m
[64X[38;2;255;255;255m
●[m[1CFound[1Cthe[1Croot[1Ccause.[1CIt's[1Cin[38;2;177;185;249m[1CComponents/mindzie.AutomatedActions/Helpers/ActionMapper.cs:216-245[m[1C(the[38;2;177;185;249m[1CUpdate[m[1Coverload).
 [1C[36X[37C[12X
  [1mRoot caus[22m[1C[32X[46;1H  The mapper applies a DTO to an already-tracked [38;2;177;185;249mTblAction [mentity. For child collections ([38;2;177;185;249mTblActionSteps[m, [38;2;177;185;249mTblActionEntities[m, [38;2;177;185;249mTblActionTriggers[m) it   does:
                                                                                                                                                   [49;3Haction.TblActionSteps = [34mnew [mList<TblActionStep>();[32m[7C// REPLACES the tracked collection[34m[50;3Hforeach[m[1C([34mvar[m[1Cdto[34m[1Cin[m[1CactionDto.ActionSteps)
      action.TblActionSteps.Add(Map(dto));[32m[18C// Adds new objects[K[68C[m
[147C
  And the per-DTO [38;2;177;185;249mMap [mat line 77:[K[114C
[147C
  ActionStepId = actionStepDto.ActionStepId == Guid.Empty ? Guid.NewGuid() : actionStepDto.ActionStepId,[43C
[147C
  [1mpreserves[22m [1mthe[22m [1mPK[22m [1mfrom[22m [1mthe[22m [1mDTO[22m. So on re-edit:[K[100C
[147C
  1. [38;2;177;185;249mFind() [mloads the TblAction + its existing steps/entities/triggers into EF's change tracker with PKs = [38;2;177;185;249m{X, Y, Z}[m.[K[30C
  2. Mapper replaces the navigation property with a brand-new [38;2;177;185;249mList<> [mand adds fresh [38;2;177;185;249mTblActionStep [mobjects with the SAME PKs [38;2;177;185;249m{X, Y, Z} [m(because the 
  DTO carried them over).[122C
  3. The old tracked children are now orphaned from the parent's collection but still live in EF's change tracker with their original state        
  ([38;2;177;185;249mUnchanged[m). The new objects enter the graph with those same PKs.[K[80C
  4. At [38;2;177;185;249mSaveChanges[m, EF issues DELETEs for the orphans and INSERTs for the new ones. The batch order and row-count check doesn't line up →[K[9C
  [1m"expected[22m [1m1[22m [1mrow(s)[22m [1maffected[22m [1mbut[22m [1maffected[22m [1m0"[22m → [38;2;177;185;249mDbUpdateConcurrencyException[m.[K[70C
[147C
  [1mFix[22m[K[142C
[147C
  Switch from "replace the collection" to "clear and refill the same collection" in [38;2;177;185;249mActionMapper.Map(UpdateActionDto, TblAction)[m:[K[18C
[147C
  action.TblActionEntities.Clear();[112C
  [34mforeach [m([34mvar [mdto [34min [mactionDto.ActionEntities)[K[100C
      action.TblActionEntities.Add(Map(dto));[102C
[147C
  action.TblActionSteps.Clear();[115C
  [34mforeach [m([34mvar [mdto [34min [mactionDto.ActionSteps)[K[103C
      action.TblActionSteps.Add(Map(dto));[105C
[147C
  action.TblActionTriggers.Clear();[112C
  [34mforeach [m([34mvar [mdto [34min [mactionDto.ActionTriggers)[K[100C
      action.TblActionTriggers.Add(Map(dto));[102C
[147C
  [38;2;177;185;249m.Clear() [mon the tracked collection tells EF "these children are leaving the relationship", which EF translates to DELETEs (via cascade) in the   
  same SaveChanges pass [1mbefore[22m processing the new [38;2;177;185;249mAdd() [mentries. This matches the pattern EF Core expects for parent-with-children updates. The PK 
  preservation in the per-DTO [38;2;177;185;249mMap [mthen becomes a correct UPDATE path for steps that survived (via EF's identity resolution) and a correct INSERT   
  path for genuinely new ones.[117C
[147C
  [1mWhy[22m [1mthis[22m [1mis[22m [1msafe:[22m[K[128C
  - No DB schema change.[123C
  - Touches one method, ~10 lines.[113C
  - Does not change the intended behavior for the [38;2;177;185;249mAddActionDto [moverload (line 11) — that one was never broken.[K[37C
  - Actions not of type "AI Process Analyst report" happen to go through the same Update path — they were likely hitting this same issue silently  
  or on specific edit patterns. This fix helps them too.[91C
[147C
  [1mNot[22m [1maddressing[22m [1min[22m [1mthis[22m [1mcommit:[22m[K[115C
  - [38;2;177;185;249mActionRepository.Update [m(the double-[38;2;177;185;249mFind [m+ [38;2;177;185;249mCurrentValues.SetValues [mpattern on what's already a tracked entity) is suboptimal but not the cause 
  of the concurrency failure. Leave it for a separate cleanup if desired.[74C
[147C
  [1mProposed[22m [1mcommit[22m[K[130C
[147C
  One file change:[129C
  - [38;2;177;185;249mComponents/mindzie.AutomatedActions/Helpers/ActionMapper.cs [m— replace the three [38;2;177;185;249mnew List<...>() [massignments with [38;2;177;185;249m.Clear() [mcalls (~9 lines      
  changed)[137C
[147C
  Single commit, closes #7278.[117C
