  [1mIssue A — "Project Tre[1C" shows not-found ✅ clear fix[22m[42;1H [1CAt [38;2;177;185;249mDatasetManagementComponent.razor.cs:1633-1636[m:[43;3H  [1C   [4C  [1C    [3C  [1C    [3C  [1C       [34m[44;3Hprivate void [mNavigateToProjectTree(TblDataset[1Cdataset)
  {                                                                                                                                                   [3CNavManager.NavigateTo([31m$"project-tree/[m{dataset.DatasetId}");
  }                                                                                                                                                [48;3H[87X
But[1Cthe[1Cpage's[1Croute[1Cat[38;2;177;185;249m[1CProjectTree_WIP_TEMP/ProjectTreePage.razor:1[m[1Cis:

  @page "/project-overview/{ProjectId:guid}"[103C
[147C
  Two mismatches:[130C
  1. Path: [38;2;177;185;249mproject-tree [mvs [38;2;177;185;249mproject-overview[K[104C[m
  2. Parameter: passing [38;2;177;185;249mDatasetId[m, page expects [38;2;177;185;249mProjectId[K[90C[m
[147C
  The page itself ([38;2;177;185;249mProjectTreePage.razor.cs[m) shows a hierarchical tree rooted at [3moriginal[23m [3mdatasets[23m [3mwithin[23m [3mthe[23m [3mproject[23m, so it needs project context 
  — [38;2;177;185;249mProjectId [mis the correct parameter.[K[108C
[147C
  [1mFix:[22m change the nav to [38;2;177;185;249m$"project-overview/{dataset.ProjectId}"[m. Two-line change, low risk.[K[55C
[147C
  [1mIssue[22m [1mB[22m [1m—[22m [1m"Update[22m [1mDataset"[22m [1mhover[22m [1msubmenu[22m [1mdoesn't[22m [1mappear[22m [1m⚠[22m [1mneeds[22m [1mlive[22m [1mrepro[22m[K[71C
[147C
  The menu uses [38;2;177;185;249mSuperDropdownHover [mwhose visibility is driven entirely by pure CSS:[K[64C
[147C
  .super-dropdown:hover .dropdown-content { display: block; }[86C
[147C
  The submenu is nested inside the main 3-dot dropdown, positioned with [38;2;177;185;249mtw-absolute tw-right-40 tw--mt-10[m. The "not appearing" could be:[K[11C
[147C
  - Hover-state racing with the parent dropdown's click-close logic[80C
  - Submenu rendering off-screen due to [38;2;177;185;249mtw-right-40 [mposition + viewport edge[K[71C
  - Blazor scoped-CSS attribute missing from [38;2;177;185;249m.dropdown-content [mat runtime[K[74C
  - z-index conflict with an overlay[111C
[147C
  All four are plausible. Diagnosing without watching the actual DOM/CSS inspector is guessing. I don't want to throw speculative CSS changes at   
  it.[142C
[147C
  [1mPlan[22m[K[141C
[147C
  [1mSplit[22m [1minto[22m [1mtwo[22m [1mfixes:[22m[K[124C
[147C
  1. [1mNow:[22m Commit the Project Tree navigation fix. One file ([38;2;177;185;249mDatasetManagementComponent.razor.cs[m), ~2 lines changed.[K[32C
  2. [1mDefer[22m [1mIssue[22m [1mB[22m with a comment on 7273 noting that the submenu-not-appearing part needs browser-console / screenshot evidence to pinpoint — same
   approach as 7276.[127C
[147C
  [1mAlternative:[22m If you'd rather I live-test Issue B on the running server (I can use the same Playwright setup from TC_7141), I can add ~30 min to  
  reproduce and diagnose before proposing a fix. But a UI-hover issue like this is hard to catch in a headless test unless I know exactly what to  
  look for.[136C
[147C
  [1mMy[22m [1mpick:[22m commit the Project Tree fix now; defer Issue B with a comment. Then we proceed to 7272.[K[49C
