  The menu uses [38;2;177;185;249mSuperDropdownHover [mwhose visibility is driven entirely by pure CSS:[K
[K
  .super-dropdown:hover .dropdown-content { display: block; }[K
[K
  The submenu is nested inside the main 3-dot dropdown, positioned with [38;2;177;185;249mtw-absolute tw-right-40 tw--mt-10[m. The "not appearing" could be:[K
[K
  - Hover-state racing with the parent dropdown's click-close logic[K
  - Submenu rendering off-screen due to [38;2;177;185;249mtw-right-40 [mposition + viewport edge[K
  - Blazor scoped-CSS attribute missing from [38;2;177;185;249m.dropdown-content [mat runtime[K
  - z-index conflict with an overlay[K
[K
  All four are plausible. Diagnosing without watching the actual DOM/CSS inspector is guessing. I don't want to throw speculative CSS changes at   
  it.[K
[K
  [1mPlan[22m[K
[K
  [1mSplit[22m [1minto[22m [1mtwo[22m [1mfixes:[22m[K
[K
  1. [1mNow:[22m Commit the Project Tree navigation fix. One file ([38;2;177;185;249mDatasetManagementComponent.razor.cs[m), ~2 lines changed.[K
  2. [1mDefer[22m [1mIssue[22m [1mB[22m with a comment on 7273 noting that the submenu-not-appearing part needs browser-console / screenshot evidence to pinpoint — same
   approach as 7276.[K
[K
  [1mAlternative:[22m If you'd rather I live-test Issue B on the running server (I can use the same Playwright setup from TC_7141), I can add ~30 min to  
  reproduce and diagnose before proposing a fix. But a UI-hover issue like this is hard to catch in a headless test unless I know exactly what to  
  look for.[K
[K
  [1mMy[22m [1mpick:[22m commit the Project Tree fix now; defer Issue B with a comment. Then we proceed to 7272.[K
